"""
An incoming HTTP request received by an HttpServer route handler.

HttpRequest objects are created by the server and passed to route
handler blocks. They provide access to the request method, path,
headers, query parameters, and body.

```example
"Inspecting a request in a handler"
server route: '/api/data' method: 'POST' handler: [:req |
    | method path body |
    method := req method.     "=> 'POST'"
    path := req path.         "=> '/api/data'"
    body := req body.         "=> request body string"
    HttpResponse new: 200 body: body
]
```

```example
"Reading headers and query parameters"
server route: '/search' method: 'GET' handler: [:req |
    | auth query |
    auth := req header: 'Authorization'.
    query := req queryParam: 'q'.
    HttpResponse new: 200 body: 'Searching for: ', query
]
```
"""
HttpRequest subclass: Object

  """
  Return the request body as a string. The body is read lazily on
  first access and cached for subsequent calls.

  ```example
  body := request body
  ```
  """
  method: body [
      <primitive>
  ]

  """
  Return the URL path of the request (e.g. '/api/data').

  ```example
  request path   "=> '/api/data'"
  ```
  """
  method: path [
      <primitive>
  ]

  """
  Return the HTTP method of the request (e.g. 'GET', 'POST').

  ```example
  request method   "=> 'GET'"
  ```
  """
  method: method [
      <primitive>
  ]

  """
  Return the value of the named HTTP header, or an empty string
  if the header is not present.

  ```example
  contentType := request header: 'Content-Type'
  ```
  """
  method: header: name [
      <primitive>
  ]

  """
  Return the value of the named URL query parameter, or an empty
  string if the parameter is not present.

  ```example
  "For URL '/search?q=hello'"
  request queryParam: 'q'   "=> 'hello'"
  ```
  """
  method: queryParam: name [
      <primitive>
  ]
